{"questionId":"9069944","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>Ethane-1,2-diol, HOCH<sub>2</sub>CH<sub>2</sub>OH, reacts with thionyl chloride, SOCl<sub>2</sub>, according to the reaction&nbsp;below.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:center;\">HOCH<sub>2</sub>CH<sub>2</sub>OH (l) + 2SOCl<sub>2</sub> (l) → ClCH<sub>2</sub>CH<sub>2</sub>Cl (l) + 2SO<sub>2</sub> (g) + 2HCl (g)</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>Calculate the standard entropy change for this reaction using the following data.</p>\n<p><img src=\"__IMG__/fd8ed7151dfc13014d2714c9041fdb3503fe8660.png\"></p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p>«Δ<em>S</em><sup>θ </sup>=&nbsp;[208.5&nbsp;+ 2(248.1)&nbsp;+ 2(186.8)] – [166.9&nbsp;+ 2(278.6)]»</p>\n<p>«Δ<em>S</em><sup>θ&nbsp;</sup>= +» 354.2 «J K<sup>–1</sup> mol<sup>–1</sup>»</p>","meta":{"questionId":"9069944","referenceCode":"17N.2.hl.TZ0.5b","subjectId":"45-dp-chemistry-last-assessment-2024","title":"Calculate the standard entropy change for this reaction using the following data.","paper":"2","level":"HL","questionNumber":"b","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 1]","breadcrumbLabels":["Additional higher level (AHL)","Additional higher level (AHL)","Topic 15: Energetics/thermochemistry","15.2 Entropy and spontaneity","Additional higher level (AHL)","Topic 15: Energetics/thermochemistry"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}